lead_paragraph: The two projectiles, believed to be Scud-C missiles, flew about 310 miles and crashed into the sea off North Korea’s east coast, a South Korean statement said.

headline.main: North Korea Fires Test Missiles, Defying U.N. Ban

snippet: The two projectiles, believed to be Scud-C missiles, flew about 310 miles and crashed into the sea off North Korea’s east coast, a South Korean statement said.
abstract: South Korean military announces North Korea launched two ballistic missiles into sea between Koreas and Japan, in violation of United Nations resolutions.
